CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Health – Chain Restaurants – Disclosure and Notice to Customers of
3 Sodium and Added Sugars Warning Icons
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Maryland Department of Health to adopt certain
5 regulations relating to the sale of food items with a high added sugars content or
6 high sodium content by a chain restaurant by a certain date and to administer a
7 certain continuing education campaign direct chain restaurants to its website within
8 a certain time for a certain purpose; requiring certain chain restaurants to display a
9 certain icons next to disclosure and notice regarding food items with a high added
10 sugars content or high sodium content on each menu or menu board; and generally
11 relating to chain restaurants and high sodium and added sugars menu icons items.
12 BY renumbering
13 Article – Health – General
14 Section 21–330.3 and 21–330.4
15 to be Section 21–330.4 and 21–330.5, respectively
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
19 Article – Education
20 Section 13–517(a)(1)
21 Annotated Code of Maryland
22 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
