21 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
22 That Section(s) 21–330.3 and 21–330.4 of Article – Health – General of the Annotated Code
23 of Maryland be renumbered to be Section(s) 21–330.4 and 21–330.5, respectively.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
25 as follows:
26 Article – Education
27 13–517.
28 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
29 (4) (i) “Facility” means an agency, an association, a corporation, a firm,
30 a partnership, or any other entity.
31 (ii) “Facility” does not include a grocery store or restaurant that is
32 subject to [§ 21–330.3] § 21–330.4 of the Health – General Article.
33 Article – Health – General
34 21–301.

SENATE BILL 866 3
1 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
2 (h) (1) “Food service facility” means:
3 (i) A place where food or drink is prepared for sale or service on the
4 premises or elsewhere; or
5 (ii) Any operation where food is served to or provided for the public,
6 with or without charge.
7 (2) “Food service facility” includes a micro market licensed under Title 17,
8 Subtitle 17 of the Business Regulation Article.
9 (3) “Food service facility” does not include:
10 (i) A kitchen in a private home where food is prepared at no charge
11 for guests in the home, for guests at a social gathering, or for service to unemployed,
12 homeless, or other disadvantaged populations;
13 (ii) A food preparation or serving area where food is prepared or
14 served only by an excluded organization;
15 (iii) A location in a farmer’s market or at a public festival or event
16 where raw agricultural products, as defined in § 21–304(d)(1)(iii) of this subtitle, are sold;
17 or
18 (iv) A cottage food business.
19 21–330.3.
20 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
21 INDICATED.
22 (2) “CHAIN RESTAURANT” MEANS A FOOD SERVICE FACILITY THAT IS:
23 (I) IS PART OF A CHAIN WITH 20 OR MORE LOCATIONS DOING
24 BUSINESS UNDER THE SAME NAME, REGARDLESS OF OWNERSHIP STRUCTURE, AND
25 OFFERING FOR SALE SUBSTANTIALLY SIMILAR MENU ITEMS; AND
26 (II) IS SUBJECT TO FEDERAL LABELING REQUIREMENTS UNDER
27 21 U.S.C. § 343(Q)(5)(H).
28 (3) “HIGH ADDED SUGARS CONTENT” MEANS 25 MILLIGRAMS GRAMS
29 OR MORE OF ADDED SUGARS PER SERVING.

4 SENATE BILL 866
1 (4) “HIGH SODIUM CONTENT” MEANS 1,150 MILLIGRAMS OR MORE OF
2 SODIUM PER SERVING.
3 (5) “MENU” OR “MENU BOARD” MEANS THE PRIMARY WRITING
4 SOURCE FROM WHICH A CUSTOMER MAKES AN ORDER SELECTION.
5 (6) “POINT OF SELECTION” MEANS A PLACE WHERE A CUSTOMER MAY
6 VIEW THE MENU AND MAKE A SELECTION TO PURCHASE A MENU ITEM.
7 (7) (6) (I) “STANDARD MENU ITEM” MEANS A FOOD OR
8 BEVERAGE ITEM THAT IS LISTED ON A MENU OR MENU BOARD.
9 (II) “STANDARD MENU ITEM” DOES NOT INCLUDE A FOOD OR
10 BEVERAGE ITEM THAT APPEARS ON A MENU OR MENU BOARD FOR LESS THAN 60
11 CALENDAR DAYS PER YEAR.
12 (B) ON OR BEFORE JANUARY 1, 2027, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADOPT
13 REGULATIONS TO:
14 (1) ESTABLISH A HIGH SODIUM CONTENT WARNING ICON AND
15 ACCOMPANYING TEXT;
16 (2) ESTABLISH A HIGH ADDED SUGARS CONTENT WARNING ICON AND
17 ACCOMPANYING TEXT;
18 (3) ESTABLISH A MINIMUM SIZE FOR EACH WARNING ICON THAT IS AT
19 LEAST AS LARGE AS THE LARGEST TEXT CHARACTER USED IN THE NAME OF THE
20 MENU ITEM THAT THE ICON WILL BE DISPLAYED NEXT TO ON THE MENU OR MENU
21 BOARD; AND
22 (4) IMPLEMENT THIS SECTION.
23 (C) CONCURRENT WITH THE ADOPTION OF REGULATIONS UNDER
24 SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL PUBLISH GUIDANCE
25 ON ITS WEBSITE THAT DETAILS THE PURPOSE OF AND HOW A CHAIN RESTAURANT
26 MAY COMPLY WITH THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS SECTION.
27 (D) DURING CALENDAR YEAR 2027, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADMINISTER
28 A CONTINUING EDUCATION CAMPAIGN THAT EXPLAINS DIRECT CHAIN
29 RESTAURANTS TO ITS WEBSITE FOR THE PURPOSE OF EXPLAINING THE PURPOSE OF
30 AND HOW A CHAIN RESTAURANT MAY COMPLY WITH THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS
31 SECTION.

SENATE BILL 866 5
1 (E) (C) BEGINNING JANUARY 1, 2028 2027, EACH CHAIN RESTAURANT IN
2 THE STATE SHALL DISPLAY ON EACH MENU OR MENU BOARD A WRITTEN
3 DISCLOSURE AND NOTICE TO CUSTOMERS THAT:
4 (1) NEXT TO EACH STANDARD MENU ITEM WITH A HIGH SODIUM
5 CONTENT, THE HIGH SODIUM CONTENT WARNING ICON AND ACCOMPANYING TEXT
6 ESTABLISHED IN REGULATIONS ADOPTED UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION
7 STANDARD MENU ITEMS MAY CONTAIN HIGH SODIUM OR HIGH SUGAR; AND
8 (2) NEXT TO EACH STANDARD MENU ITEM WITH A HIGH ADDED
9 SUGARS CONTENT, THE HIGH ADDED SUGARS CONTENT WARNING ICON AND
10 ACCOMPANYING TEXT ESTABLISHED IN REGULATIONS ADOPTED UNDER
11 SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION FULL NUTRITIONAL INFORMATION IS AVAILABLE
12 THROUGH A QUICK RESPONSE (QR) CODE, ONLINE, OR BY REQUEST.
13 (D) A CHAIN RESTAURANT MAY COMPLY WITH SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS
14 SECTION BY MAKING THE FULL NUTRITIONAL INFORMATION OF THE FOOD OR
15 BEVERAGE ITEM AVAILABLE:
16 (1) THROUGH USE OF A QUICK RESPONSE (QR) CODE THAT LINKS TO
17 THE CHAIN RESTAURANT’S ONLINE NUTRITIONAL INFORMATION; AND
18 (2) ON REQUEST OF A CUSTOMER, IN ANY PRINTED FORMAT.
19 (F) (1) IF THE CHAIN RESTAURANT IS REQUIRED TO DISPLAY A WARNING
20 ICON AND ACCOMPANYING TEXT UNDER SUBSECTION (E)(1) OF THIS SECTION, THE
21 FOLLOWING TEXT SHALL BE PROMINENTLY, CLEARLY, AND CONSPICUOUSLY
22 DISPLAYED AT THE POINT OF SELECTION LEAST ONCE ON EACH MENU OR MENU
23 BOARD:
24 “THE HIGH SODIUM CONTENT WARNING ICON INDICATES A MENU ITEM WITH
25 A SODIUM (SALT) CONTENT THAT EXCEEDS HALF THE TOTAL DAILY RECOMMENDED
26 LIMIT. DIETS HIGHER IN SODIUM ARE ASSOCIATED WITH AN INCREASED RISK OF
27 DEVELOPING HIGH BLOOD PRESSURE, WHICH IS A MAJOR CAUSE OF HEART DISEASE
28 AND STROKE.”.
29 (2) IF THE CHAIN RESTAURANT IS REQUIRED TO DISPLAY A WARNING
30 ICON AND ACCOMPANYING TEXT UNDER SUBSECTION (E)(2) OF THIS SECTION, THE
31 FOLLOWING TEXT SHALL BE PROMINENTLY, CLEARLY, AND CONSPICUOUSLY
32 DISPLAYED AT THE POINT OF SELECTION LEAST ONCE ON EACH MENU OR MENU
33 BOARD:

6 SENATE BILL 866
1 “THE HIGH ADDED SUGARS CONTENT WARNING ICON INDICATES A MENU ITEM
2 WITH A SUGAR CONTENT THAT EXCEEDS HALF THE TOTAL DAILY RECOMMENDED
3 LIMIT. DIETS WITH HIGHER AMOUNTS OF ADDED SUGARS OVER TIME MAY INCREASE
4 THE RISK OF TYPE 2 DIABETES, WEIGHT GAIN, AND TOOTH DECAY.”.
5 (G) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1, 2032, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL SUBMIT A
6 REPORT TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE
7 STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THAT:
8 (1) REVIEWS ANY EVIDENCE OF THE IMPACT OF THE REQUIREMENTS
9 ESTABLISHED UNDER THIS SECTION, INCLUDING:
10 (I) WHETHER AND TO WHAT EXTENT ANY STANDARD MENU
11 ITEMS WERE REFORMULATED; AND
12 (II) WHETHER AND HOW CONSUMER BEHAVIOR CHANGED; AND
13 (2) RECOMMENDS ANY ADDITIONAL NUTRITION–RELATED MENU
14 WARNING ICONS THAT SHOULD BE CONSIDERED.
15 21–1214.
16 (a) (1) Except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection, any person who
17 violates any provision of Subtitle 3 of this title or any rule or regulation adopted under
18 Subtitle 3 of this title is guilty of a misdemeanor and on conviction is subject to:
19 (i) For a first offense, a fine not exceeding $1,000 or imprisonment
20 not exceeding 90 days, or both; and
21 (ii) For a second offense, a fine not exceeding $2,500 or imprisonment
22 not exceeding 1 year, or both.
23 (2) A person who violates § 21–330.1 OR § 21–330.3 of this title is not
24 subject to paragraph (1) of this subsection.
25 (b) In addition to any criminal penalties imposed under this section, a person who
26 violates any provision of Subtitle 3 of this title or any rule or regulation adopted under
27 Subtitle 3 of this title or any term, condition, or limitation of any license or registration
28 issued under Subtitle 3 of this title:
29 (1) Is liable for a civil penalty not exceeding $5,000, to be collected in a civil
30 action in the District Court for any county; and
31 (2) May be enjoined from continuing the violation.

SENATE BILL 866 7
1 (c) Each day on which a violation occurs is a separate violation under this section.
2 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
3 1, 2026.
